<blockquote>
  <p>The 4-partition limit no longer exists with disks that use the GUID
Partition Table (GPT). GPT supports up to 128 partitions by default
and does not include the concepts of primary, extended, or logical
partitions (although many tools refer to all GPT partitions as
“primary partitions,” simply because those tools were written with
the older MBR system in mind). <a href="https://askubuntu.com/questions/149821/my-disk-already-has-4-primary-partitions-how-can-i-install-ubuntu?utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_source=google_rich_qa&amp;utm_campaign=google_rich_qa">-askubuntu</a></p>
</blockquote>

